title: "The Shape of Discovery: Detecting Topological Precursors to Technological Breakthroughs in the USPTO Patent Citation Network"
abstract: >-
  Applies persistent homology to the U.S. patent citation network (~8M patents,
  ~118M citations, 1976-2023) to test whether topological signatures precede
  technological breakthroughs. Key findings: (1) beta-1 (topological loops) shows
  no systematic precursor signal (p=0.48); (2) persistence entropy also non-significant
  (p=0.14); (3) no test survives Holm-Bonferroni correction — a clean null result;
  (4) topological features carry cross-domain predictive signal comparable to simple
  features (LOGO LR AUC 0.80 vs 0.82). Conceptual design, analytical framework,
  and implementation by Claude (Opus 4.6, Anthropic). Facilitated by Christopher Ortiz.
version: v1.2.0
